                            <comment id="16641645" author="paulk" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2018 10:48:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This doesn&apos;t occur if only the method has @CompileStatic like in this script:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.*

@Field &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; foo = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;FOO&apos;&lt;/span&gt;

@CompileStatic
void test() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Runnable&lt;/span&gt;() {
        void run() {
            def c = {
                println foo
            }
            c()
        }
    } .run()
}

test()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or in this class:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.*

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;GroovyTest {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; foo = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;FOO&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
    @CompileStatic
    void test() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Runnable&lt;/span&gt;() {
            void run() {
                def c = {
                    println foo
                }
                c()
            }
        }.run()
    }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; GroovyTest().test()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basically the inner closure will be dynamic code in those cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16642618" author="paulk" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2018 23:55:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Workaround is to prefix the method call, e.g. &lt;tt&gt;this.println&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;println&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.*

@CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;GroovyTest {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; foo = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;FOO&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
    void test() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Runnable&lt;/span&gt;() {
            void run() {
                def c = {
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.println foo
                }
                c()
            }
        }.run()
    }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; GroovyTest().test()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16644921" author="paulk" created="Wed, 10 Oct 2018 12:43:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should be fixed in the next release. Thanks for reporting the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
